.TH "r600_mmio_hdp_flush" 9 "r600_mmio_hdp_flush" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
r600_mmio_hdp_flush \- flush Host Data Path cache via MMIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" r600_mmio_hdp_flush
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon device structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Some R6XX/R7XX don't seem to take into account HDP flushes performed
through the ring buffer. This leads to corruption in rendering, see
http://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15186 . To avoid this, we
directly perform the HDP flush by writing the register through MMIO.
